cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on visual tracking for robot manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also extensively uses computer vision techniques such as correlation filters and appearance models, which makes cs.CV a likely sub-category as well. The learning-based tracker also suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with image sequences and their analysis, which could also make multimedia (cs.MM) a possible sub-category.
